obo:GO_0099507  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_1337  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: WC patch-clamp current measurements of beta1 containing GABAR's expressed in HEK cells.\n\nrule: NAS_MFCC-BP\nrationale:\nProtein has ligand-gated ion channel receptor activity and is localized in the presynaptic membrane (shown with high-resolution technique). The inference to term ligand-gated ion channel activity involved in regulation of presynaptic membrane potential (GO:0099507) is trivial and non-controversial.\nPinf_CC:\n[P15431] SyNGO ID 1269 (PMID:14686901, EM)\n[P15431] SyNGO ID 1274 (PMID:15174078, EM). Experimental description: Complementary DNA Constructs\nThe complementary DNAs (cDNAs) encoding human GABAA receptor subunits a1 (NM_000806.5), b1 (NM_000812.3), b3 (NM_021912.4 variant 2), c2L (NM_198904.2), and EGFP (LC008490.1) were cloned into the pcDNA3.1(1) vector." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9425-2935" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_MF_1337" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .

